{
  "quality_level": "A",
  "sections": [
    {
      "id": "sec-0",
      "heading": {
        "number": "",
        "title": "Abstract"
      },
      "blocks": [
        {
          "id": "blk-0-p1-5d87",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlines": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "We present "
            },
            {
              "t": "emphasis",
              "v": "rectified flow"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", a surprisingly simple approach to learning transport maps between two distributions "
            },
            {
              "t": "math_inline",
              "v": "\\pi_0"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and "
            },
            {
              "t": "math_inline",
              "v": "\\pi_1"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", by connecting samples with straight paths and following the ordinary differential equation "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "式(1)",
              "ref": "eq-1",
              "kind": "equation"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". The method unifies generative modeling and domain transfer, and its recursive "
            },
            {
              "t": "emphasis",
              "v": "reflow"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " procedure straightens the paths so that a single Euler step suffices "
            },
            {
              "t": "citation",
              "v": "",
              "ref": "liu2022flow"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ],
          "caption": [],
          "items": []
        }
      ],
      "sections": []
    },
    {
      "id": "sec-1",
      "heading": {
        "number": "1",
        "title": "Introduction"
      },
      "blocks": [
        {
          "id": "blk-1-p1-c4d1",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlines": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Generative modeling and domain transfer both require transporting one distribution to another. Continuous-time methods such as diffusion models "
            },
            {
              "t": "citation",
              "v": "",
              "ref": "ho2020denoising"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and score-based SDEs "
            },
            {
              "t": "citation",
              "v": "",
              "ref": "song2021scorebased"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " achieve strong results but rely on curved trajectories that are expensive to simulate"
            },
            {
              "t": "footnote_ref",
              "v": "",
              "ref": "fn-1"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". We instead learn "
            },
            {
              "t": "emphasis",
              "v": "straight"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " trajectories; see "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "図1",
              "ref": "fig-1",
              "kind": "figure"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ],
          "caption": [],
          "items": []
        },
        {
          "id": "blk-1-fig1-fe1c",
          "type": "figure",
          "inlines": [],
          "number": "1",
          "label": "fig-1",
          "asset_key": "figures/fig-1.png",
          "caption": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Straightening effect of "
            },
            {
              "t": "emphasis",
              "v": "reflow"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ": trajectories learned by rectified flow become nearly straight after one reflow step, enabling one-step generation."
            }
          ],
          "items": []
        },
        {
          "id": "blk-1-p2-0b4e",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlines": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Our reference implementation is available at "
            },
            {
              "t": "url",
              "v": "github.com/gnobitab/RectifiedFlow",
              "href": "https://github.com/gnobitab/RectifiedFlow"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". The core training loop reduces to a single call to "
            },
            {
              "t": "code_inline",
              "v": "F.mse_loss(v_theta(z_t, t), x1 - x0)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", i.e. a least-squares regression onto the constant velocity direction."
            }
          ],
          "caption": [],
          "items": []
        },
        {
          "id": "blk-1-li1-5089",
          "type": "list",
          "inlines": [],
          "caption": [],
          "ordered": true,
          "items": [
            [
              {
                "t": "text",
                "v": "A unified least-squares objective for generation and transfer."
              }
            ],
            [
              {
                "t": "text",
                "v": "A "
              },
              {
                "t": "emphasis",
                "v": "reflow"
              },
              {
                "t": "text",
                "v": " operator that straightens flows and reduces transport cost."
              }
            ],
            [
              {
                "t": "text",
                "v": "A "
              },
              {
                "t": "emphasis",
                "v": "distillation"
              },
              {
                "t": "text",
                "v": " scheme yielding high-quality one-step generators."
              }
            ]
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "blk-1-fn1-5b23",
          "type": "footnote",
          "inlines": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Simulating a curved ODE typically requires tens to hundreds of network evaluations, which dominates sampling cost."
            }
          ],
          "caption": [],
          "items": []
        }
      ],
      "sections": []
    },
    {
      "id": "sec-2",
      "heading": {
        "number": "2",
        "title": "Method"
      },
      "blocks": [
        {
          "id": "blk-2-p1-65ad",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlines": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "We first define rectified flow, then present the "
            },
            {
              "t": "emphasis",
              "v": "reflow"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and "
            },
            {
              "t": "emphasis",
              "v": "distillation"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " procedures that make sampling fast."
            }
          ],
          "caption": [],
          "items": []
        },
        {
          "id": "blk-2-h1-f18b",
          "type": "heading",
          "inlines": [],
          "level": 3,
          "number": "2.0",
          "title": "Notation",
          "caption": [],
          "items": []
        }
      ],
      "sections": [
        {
          "id": "sec-2-1",
          "heading": {
            "number": "2.1",
            "title": "Rectified Flow"
          },
          "blocks": [
            {
              "id": "blk-2-1-p1-9eca",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlines": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Given empirical draws "
                },
                {
                  "t": "math_inline",
                  "v": "X_0 \\sim \\pi_0"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " and "
                },
                {
                  "t": "math_inline",
                  "v": "X_1 \\sim \\pi_1"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", the linear interpolation "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "式(1)",
                  "ref": "eq-1",
                  "kind": "equation"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " defines a time-indexed path whose velocity is constant."
                }
              ],
              "caption": [],
              "items": []
            },
            {
              "id": "blk-2-1-eq1-ff46",
              "type": "equation",
              "inlines": [],
              "number": "1",
              "label": "eq-1",
              "caption": [],
              "latex": "X_t = t\\,X_1 + (1-t)\\,X_0,\\quad t \\in [0,1]",
              "items": []
            },
            {
              "id": "blk-2-1-eq2-2dfc",
              "type": "equation",
              "inlines": [],
              "number": "2",
              "label": "eq-2",
              "caption": [],
              "latex": "\\min_{\\theta}\\ \\int_0^1 \\mathbb{E}\\big[\\, \\lVert (X_1 - X_0) - v_\\theta(X_t, t) \\rVert^2 \\,\\big]\\, dt",
              "items": []
            },
            {
              "id": "blk-2-1-p2-42e6",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlines": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Solving the ODE "
                },
                {
                  "t": "math_inline",
                  "v": "dZ_t = v_\\theta(Z_t, t)\\, dt"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " from "
                },
                {
                  "t": "math_inline",
                  "v": "Z_0 \\sim \\pi_0"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " transports mass toward the target. The learned velocity is the conditional expectation of the straight-line direction."
                }
              ],
              "caption": [],
              "items": []
            },
            {
              "id": "blk-2-1-thm1-2ee5",
              "type": "theorem",
              "inlines": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The rectified flow induced by any coupling preserves the marginal distributions and never increases the expected transport cost, for every convex cost "
                },
                {
                  "t": "math_inline",
                  "v": "c(\\cdot)"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ],
              "caption": [],
              "items": []
            },
            {
              "id": "blk-2-1-eq3-9d5a",
              "type": "equation",
              "inlines": [],
              "number": "3",
              "label": "eq-3",
              "caption": [],
              "latex": "\\mathbb{E}\\big[c(Z_1 - Z_0)\\big] \\le \\mathbb{E}\\big[c(X_1 - X_0)\\big]",
              "items": []
            },
            {
              "id": "blk-2-1-q1-551d",
              "type": "quote",
              "inlines": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Straight paths are the only paths that can be simulated exactly with a single Euler step."
                }
              ],
              "caption": [],
              "items": []
            }
          ],
          "sections": []
        },
        {
          "id": "sec-2-2",
          "heading": {
            "number": "2.2",
            "title": "Reflow and Distillation"
          },
          "blocks": [
            {
              "id": "blk-2-2-p1-e102",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlines": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The "
                },
                {
                  "t": "emphasis",
                  "v": "reflow"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " operator re-couples the endpoints produced by a trained flow and re-fits the velocity, yielding straighter trajectories. Repeated reflow followed by "
                },
                {
                  "t": "emphasis",
                  "v": "distillation"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " produces a one-step model; see "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "式(4)",
                  "ref": "eq-4",
                  "kind": "equation"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ],
              "caption": [],
              "items": []
            },
            {
              "id": "blk-2-2-alg1-5154",
              "type": "algorithm",
              "inlines": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Algorithm 1 Reflow: (1) sample Z0; (2) integrate v_theta to get Z1; (3) recouple (Z0, Z1); (4) minimize the objective in Eq. (2); (5) repeat K times."
                }
              ],
              "caption": [],
              "items": []
            },
            {
              "id": "blk-2-2-eq4-3591",
              "type": "equation",
              "inlines": [],
              "number": "4",
              "label": "eq-4",
              "caption": [],
              "latex": "v^{k+1} = \\arg\\min_v \\int_0^1 \\mathbb{E}\\big[\\lVert (Z_1^{k} - Z_0^{k}) - v(Z_t^{k}, t)\\rVert^2\\big]\\, dt",
              "items": []
            },
            {
              "id": "blk-2-2-code1-a84a",
              "type": "code",
              "inlines": [],
              "caption": [],
              "language": "python",
              "code": "def reflow_step(v_theta, x0, x1, t):\n    z_t = t * x1 + (1 - t) * x0\n    target = x1 - x0\n    return F.mse_loss(v_theta(z_t, t), target)\n",
              "items": []
            },
            {
              "id": "blk-2-2-tbl1-9653",
              "type": "table",
              "inlines": [],
              "number": "1",
              "label": "tbl-1",
              "caption": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "FID on CIFAR-10 versus number of function evaluations (NFE); "
                },
                {
                  "t": "emphasis",
                  "v": "distillation"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " enables one-step sampling."
                }
              ],
              "items": [],
              "cells": [
                [
                  "Method",
                  "NFE",
                  "FID"
                ],
                [
                  "Rectified Flow",
                  "127",
                  "2.58"
                ],
                [
                  "+ reflow",
                  "1",
                  "4.85"
                ],
                [
                  "+ distillation",
                  "1",
                  "4.31"
                ]
              ]
            }
          ],
          "sections": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "sec-3",
      "heading": {
        "number": "3",
        "title": "Experiments"
      },
      "blocks": [
        {
          "id": "blk-3-p1-01e0",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlines": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "We evaluate rectified flow on unconditional image generation and image-to-image transfer. Following common practice we track an "
            },
            {
              "t": "emphasis",
              "v": "EMA teacher"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " of the weights to stabilize "
            },
            {
              "t": "emphasis",
              "v": "distillation"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and report FID against "
            },
            {
              "t": "citation",
              "v": "",
              "ref": "song2021scorebased"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "表2",
              "ref": "tbl-2",
              "kind": "table"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ],
          "caption": [],
          "items": []
        },
        {
          "id": "blk-3-fig2-aaee",
          "type": "figure",
          "inlines": [],
          "number": "2",
          "label": "fig-2",
          "asset_key": "figures/fig-2.png",
          "caption": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Samples generated in a single Euler step after two reflow rounds and "
            },
            {
              "t": "emphasis",
              "v": "distillation"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ],
          "items": []
        },
        {
          "id": "blk-3-tbl2-2f67",
          "type": "table",
          "inlines": [],
          "number": "2",
          "label": "tbl-2",
          "caption": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Comparison against diffusion baselines on CIFAR-10 and CelebA-HQ."
            }
          ],
          "items": [],
          "cells": [
            [
              "Dataset",
              "Baseline FID",
              "Ours (1-step) FID"
            ],
            [
              "CIFAR-10",
              "3.17",
              "4.31"
            ],
            [
              "CelebA-HQ",
              "7.60",
              "8.02"
            ]
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "blk-3-p2-55a9",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlines": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The one-step generator retains most of the quality of the full ODE solver while cutting sampling cost by two orders of magnitude, confirming the straightening hypothesis of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "§2.1",
              "ref": "sec-2-1",
              "kind": "section"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ],
          "caption": [],
          "items": []
        }
      ],
      "sections": []
    },
    {
      "id": "sec-4",
      "heading": {
        "number": "4",
        "title": "Conclusion"
      },
      "blocks": [
        {
          "id": "blk-4-p1-b79d",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlines": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Rectified flow offers a simple, unified, and efficient route to generative modeling and transport. Its straight trajectories make one-step generation practical without sacrificing sample quality."
            }
          ],
          "caption": [],
          "items": []
        }
      ],
      "sections": []
    },
